                  </hi>. I am an omnibus proprietor. I bought the prison<lb></lb>er's business and employed him afterwards—he was employed to collect money for me—he was to pay it to me on a Saturday night—I afterwards took the book over to Miss Jackson—the prisoner told me he had not paid me an amount of 50<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. from about forty customers—he admitted he had not paid them—if he received 8*. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. from Mr. Powell, 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. from Mr. Palmer, and 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. from Mr. Neal, he has not paid those sums to me—he ought to have paid them to me, or to Miss Jackson.</p>
